plication_of_statistics" title=3D"List of fields of application of statisti=
cs">List of fields of application of statistics</a></div>
<p>Statistical techniques are used in a wide range of types of scientific a=
nd social research, including: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bio=
statistics" title=3D"Biostatistics">biostatistics</a>, <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_biology" title=3D"Computational biology"=
>computational biology</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comput=
ational_sociology" title=3D"Computational sociology">computational sociolog=
y</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_biology" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Network biology">network biology</a>, <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_science" title=3D"Social science">social sc=
ience</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sociology" title=3D"Soc=
iology">sociology</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_r=
esearch" title=3D"Social research">social research</a>. Some fields of inqu=
iry use applied statistics so extensively that they have <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Specialized_terminology" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Specialized terminology">specialized terminology</a>. These disciplines=
 include:
</p>
